This paper is primarily focused on developing machine learning algorithms for detecting insider threats, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of various classifiers and their performance, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of performance rankings and cross-validation, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of data balancing techniques to address the relative rarity of threats, which is related to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
